social anxiety i am scared to death to go to school sometimes i never talk to anyone and i always want to be in the back or in a corner were i cant be sceen when i get called on to read or something my heart stops what do i do a few years ago i was just like you i always sat in the back of the classroom and i avoided being the center of attention it was so bad that when i had to give presentations in med school i would have to go to the bathroom and just pace until it was my turn to present i couldn't stand the waiting just knowing that i was going to have to speak in front of the class heres the bad news i had a breakdown and went to counseling and began taking zoloft i am not proud of this but it worked now while i dont relish it i have no problem speaking in front of groups or raising my hand etc finally here is the good news i am very successful both financially and professionally but had i not gone to counseling to realize why i was afflicted with social anxiety disease sad i would never have accomplished what has made me into the person that i am today so don't fear those feeling embrace them and get help it will hurt in the short run but in the long run you will be soo happy that you dealt with your anxiety there is no shame in having this affliction but get help trust me you can overcome those fears and get back on track with your life if i can do it anyone can ps there are times when it hits me but i have learned strategies and have gained the confidence to say no problem just my anxiety acting up again utilize a coping strategy and then go on with the rest of my day ps when i started telling my teachers that i had social anxiety it was amazing how many of them have it also Anxiety Clinical depression Shaggy dog story Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Kodocha Stuttering One Tree Hill (TV series) Avenue Q 2000 Australian Grand Prix Yoga Sutras of Patanjali Social rule Theory of conduct The Ashlee Simpson Show Boston Public Pitaten Plame affair Charles Darwin's ill